criteria.textblock:
        Inclusion Criteria:

          -  patients undergoing intestinal resection of all macroscopic disease, with an
             endoscopically accessible anastomosis,

        Exclusion Criteria:

          -  patients have an anastomosis which is endoscopically inaccessible by standard
             colonoscopy;

          -  patients withs persisting macroscopic abnormality after surgical resection;

          -  patients with an end stoma (ileostomy or colostomy);

          -  patients are not suitable to undergo endoscopy because of co-morbidities or an unwell
             clinical state;

          -  patients who are unable to give informed consent;

          -  patients who are pregnant
